SIMPLE: loser
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Loser
<hw>Los"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
loses; <as>as, the <ex>loser</ex> pays for a round of beer</as>.</def>
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person who is habitually unsuccessful at some
endeavor, such as employment or personal relationships.</def>
<mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A plan or strategy unlikely to succeed.</def>
<mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Losing</ent>⟦br⟧
